   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE THE GOD-MEN AND THE OVERCOMERS Scripture Reading: Rev 2:7, 11, 17, 26; 3:5, 12, 21 OUTLINE The God-men: Born of God to overcome sin and the world 1 John 3:9; 5:4.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Destined by God to conquer all the oppositions and persecutions, the hard environments, and the difficult situations Rom 8:31, 36-39.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Called by the Lord among the churches to be the overcomers Rev 2:7, 11, 17, 26; 3:5, 12, 21.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The overcomers: To overcome in the degradation of the churches: The satanic Judaism Rev 2:9-10.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The demonic Catholicism 2:24-28.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The dead and Christless Protestantism 3:1-5, 20-21.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The tide of the church's degradation.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To overcome also: Satan 12:11a.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The love of the soul-life 12:11b.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The upcoming Antichrist and his false prophet in the great tribulation 15:2; 17:14.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The way for the God-men to be the overcomers: To love Christ and follow Him John 21:15-17, 19b.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>To pursue Christ and gain Him Phil 3:12-15.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>To be conformed to the death of Christ by the power of His resurrection Phil 3:10.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>To live Christ and magnify Him by the bountiful supply of His all-inclusive Spirit Phil 1:19-21.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>To live with Christ and labor with Him Gal 2:20a; Col 1:29.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>To live the Body life and build up the Body of Christ for the fulfillment of God's New Testament economy Eph 4:12, 16; 1:10.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>The reward for the overcoming God-men, the overcomers, in the millennial kingdom: In the present age to dine with the Lord Rev 3:20b.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>At the earliest appearing of Christ to be given the morning star, signifying the precious Christ in His earliest appearing Rev 2:28.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>In the millennial kingdom: To enter richly into the kingdom of Christ 2 Pet 1:11; Matt 19:23; Acts 14:22; 2 Thes 1:5; Heb 12:28; James 2:5; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>1 Cor 6:9; Gal 5:21; Eph 5:5.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>To partake of the wedding feast of Christ, which will last for one thousand years as a day Rev 19:9; Matt 25:10.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>To have their names confessed before the Father and His angels by the Lord Rev 3:5c.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Not to have their names erased out of the book of life, to have their names erased out of the book of life in the kingdom age signifying a kind of discipline in the kingdom age Rev 3:5b.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Not to be hurt of the second death, to be hurt of the second death probably signifying also a kind of discipline in the kingdom age Rev 2:11.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>To participate in the consummation and enjoyment of the New Jerusalem as the Paradise of God in its initial stage in the millennium Rev 2:7.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>To share in the joy of the Lord Matt 25:21, 23.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>To be crowned with the crown, the crown of life and the crown of righteousness Rev 3:11; 1 Cor 9:25; Rev 2:10; James 1:12; 2 Tim 4:8.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>To sit with the Lord on His throne Rev 3:21.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>To have authority over the nations Rev 2:26-27.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>To be priests of God and of Christ and reign with Christ in the millennial kingdom Rev 20:4-6; 2 Tim 2:12.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>To eat of the tree of life in the New Jerusalem in its initial stage in the millennial kingdom Rev 2:7.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>To eat the hidden manna Rev 2:17a.</S>
   <S PAR='33' RSNT='1' SNO='33'>To be clothed with white garments Rev 3:4-5a.</S>
   <S PAR='34' RSNT='1' SNO='34'>To be a pillar in the temple of God and never to go out anymore Rev 3:12a.</S>
   <S PAR='35' RSNT='1' SNO='35'>To be given a white stone with a new name written upon it Rev 2:17b.</S>
   <S PAR='36' RSNT='1' SNO='36'>To have the name of God and the name of the city of God the New Jerusalem and the Lord's new name written upon them Rev 3:12b.</S>
   <S PAR='37' RSNT='1' SNO='37'>To be given the responsibilities in the coming kingdom Matt 24:47; 25:21a, 23a.</S>
   <S PAR='38' RSNT='1' SNO='38'>To enjoy the kingdom rest Heb 4:1, 9-11.</S>
   <S PAR='39' RSNT='1' SNO='39'>To enjoy the salvation of the soul, which is the aggregate of the above nineteen points Matt 16:25; Luke 9:24; Heb 10:39; 1 Pet 1:9-10.</S>
   <S PAR='40' RSNT='1' SNO='40'>The blessing of God's complete salvation, that is, the enjoyment of the eternal life Matt 19:29; Rom 5:21 for all the God-men in the new heaven and new earth: To participate in the holy city the New Jerusalem in its consummated stage as their temple the Triune God Himself for their dwelling in eternity Rev 22:14b; 21:22.</S>
   <S PAR='41' RSNT='1' SNO='41'>To eat the tree of life Rev 22:14a, 2.</S>
   <S PAR='42' RSNT='1' SNO='42'>To enjoy the spring of life and drink the water of life in the river of life Rev 21:6; 22:1.</S>
   <S PAR='43' RSNT='1' SNO='43'>To have God as their God and to be sons of God Rev 21:7.</S>
   <S PAR='44' RSNT='1' SNO='44'>To participate in the divine and human marriage life of the processed and consummated Triune God and the transformed and glorified tripartite man Rev 21:9.</S>
   <S PAR='45' RSNT='1' SNO='45'>To serve God as priests and to reign as kings over the nations forever and ever Rev 22:3b, 5b.</S>
   <S PAR='46' RSNT='1' SNO='46'>To have no curse and no night but to enjoy God's shining as their light Rev 22:3, 5; 21:25, 23.</S>
   <S PAR='47' RSNT='1' SNO='47'>The destiny of all "Christians": The Catholic Church as the great Babylon will be burned Rev 17:5, 16.</S>
   <S PAR='48' RSNT='1' SNO='48'>The false Christians, the tares, in all kinds of churches will be bound into bundles to be burned up in the lake of fire Matt 13:30, 40-42.</S>
   <S PAR='49' RSNT='1' SNO='49'>The genuine but defeated believers: Their work and conduct as wood, grass, and stubble will be burned at the Lord's coming.</S>
   <S PAR='50' RSNT='1' SNO='50'>They themselves will be saved, yet so as through fire 1 Cor 3:12-15.</S>
   <S PAR='51' RSNT='1' SNO='51'>They will be disciplined Matt 25:30 and transformed to be mature and perfect so that they will be qualified to participate in the New Jerusalem in its consummated stage for eternity.</S>
   <S PAR='52' RSNT='1' SNO='52'>The genuine and overcoming believers, the overcomers, whose work and conduct are like gold, silver, and precious stones: They will be rewarded 1 Cor 3:12-15; Rom 14:10; 2 Cor 5:10; 1 Cor 4:5; Matt 25:19 to enter into the coming millennial kingdom to reign with the Lord and partake of His joy, as revealed in the above list of their rewards.</S>
   <S PAR='53' RSNT='1' SNO='53'>They will be joined by the God-men perfected in the millennial kingdom in the participation of the final consummation and enjoyment of the New Jerusalem in its consummated stage for eternity.</S>
   </TEXT>
